@startuml ProbationClassification_MainFlow
title Probation Classification - Main Flow

skinparam backgroundColor #FFFFFF
skinparam handwritten false
skinparam defaultFontName Arial
skinparam defaultFontSize 12
skinparam titleFontSize 16
skinparam titleFontStyle bold

|JobService|
start
:POST /api/classificationJobs/scanningProbationClassification;
note right
  Batch size parameter
  Ex: batchSize = 5000
end note

:Execute(batchSize);
:Validate batchSize > 0;

if (Valid?) then (yes)
  :JobRun(batchSize);
else (no)
  :Log Error - Invalid Batch Size;
  stop
endif

|Do-While Loop|
note right
  **Pagination Loop**:
  Continue until all probation customers processed
  Uses system parameters for progress tracking
end note

repeat
  |Service Layer|
  :Start();
  note right
    Initialize ProbationModel
  end note

  :GetProbationCustForScanning(batchSize);
  note right
    **Get Probation Customers**:
    - FROM CTSCustomerClassification
    - WHERE ProbationEndDate > NOW()
    - AND CustID > LastCustID (pagination)
    - ORDER BY CustID, CategoryID
    - LIMIT batchSize
    
    **System Parameters Used**:
    - DailyProbation_LastCustID (start point)
    - DailyProbation_LastCategoryID
    
    **Returns**:
    - ProbationEntity[] (CustId, SportGroupId)
    - LastCustID (output parameter)
    - LastCategoryID (output parameter)
  end note

  if (Has probation customers?) then (yes)
    :ClassifyProbation();
    note right
      **Re-Classify Probation Customers**:
      1. Convert CustIDs to comma-separated string
      2. Call SP: CTS_GeneralNormalClassification_Probation_Preprocess
      
      **Re-Classification Logic**:
      - Get performance during probation
      - Calculate new metrics:
        * Turnover during probation
        * Winloss during probation
        * BetCount during probation
        * ActiveDays during probation
      - Determine category change:
        * PA → PotentialPA (improved)
        * PA → Normal (significantly improved)
        * PotentialPA → PA (deteriorated)
        * PotentialPA → Normal (improved)
        * No change (maintain current)
      - Update CTSCustomerClassification
      - Complete probation if end date reached
      - Extend probation if still PA/PotentialPA
    end note
  else (no)
    note right
      **No probation customers**:
      All customers processed
      or no customers in probation
    end note
  endif

  :UpdateLastScanDate();
  note right
    **Update System Parameters**:
    1. Update DailyProbation_LastCustID
       - Set to LastCustID from SP output
    2. Update DailyProbation_LastCategoryID
       - Set to LastCategoryID from SP output
    
    **Return isContinue**:
    - true: CustProbations has data (more to process)
    - false: CustProbations is empty (all done)
    
    **Pagination Logic**:
    Next iteration starts from:
    - CustID > LastCustID
    - CategoryID > LastCategoryID (secondary key)
  end note

  :Set isContinue flag;

repeat while (isContinue = true?) is (yes)
-> no;

|JobService|
:Complete;
note right
  **Job Completion**:
  All probation customers processed
  System parameters updated to latest position
  Ready for next job run
end note

note right
  **Key Characteristics**:
  
  1. **Do-While Loop** (not recursive):
     - Simple loop structure
     - Continues until all probation customers processed
     - No recursive calls
  
  2. **Pagination with System Parameters**:
     - LastCustID and LastCategoryID persisted
     - Survives job restarts
     - Enables resumable processing
     - No risk of re-processing
  
  3. **Simple Processing**:
     - No batch chunking (processes all at once)
     - No parallel processing
     - Straightforward sequential flow
  
  4. **No External Push**:
     - Classification changes internal only
     - No push to MainDB
     - No external API calls
  
  5. **Probation Review**:
     - Re-classifies customers in probation
     - Based on performance during probation
     - Can upgrade, downgrade, or maintain category
  
  **Comparison with DailyProblemClassification**:
  - DailyProblem: Recursive, queue-based, with external push
  - Probation: Do-while, parameter-based, internal only
end note

stop

@enduml

